rComments: Best teacher I have had in my life! The technical analysis course is amazing.
His bitcoin course is the best and he is the best instructor in my life. Will take his technical and fundamental analysis course.
excellent course and will take his algo trading workshop
His classes are very informal and his lectures and notes are helpful so that I don't have to read everything from scratch.  I will definitely take his level 2 course.

Took this guy's technical analysis course and option course before and the FRM is the third one. Overall the FRM course is less exciting which is expected as an exam prep course. Overall I like his course bcoz he brings in his front-line working experiences into the lecture as well, rather than just pure academic. But you'll needa put the work in!

Just completed the FRM level I course with this instructor. To be fair, I like the handout format better than presentation because I would not have time to read the textbook again for sure. So his handout provides a good background for you to learn the concept quickly and then DO LOTS OF EXERCISE QUESTIONs! As the ultimate goal is to PASS THE TEST!
He is very knowledgeable about the subject and he brings a lot of real-life experience to the course.

This guy speaks very rapidly with quite thick Chinese accent which makes him tough to understand. The information he is giving is copied from the text book and he is basically reading from the board the stuff you could find in the book by yourself. Wouldn't recommend to anyone.

I took his course Passing the Financial Risk Management exams. His speech is very unstructured. He has heavy accent.  He doesn't use any presentations, but he is using printouts, which are sometimes copy-past from Schweser book in a very brief format.
